author: Mark Brus For Metro.Co.Uk
title: Arsenal news: Sutton FA Cup tie has legend worried | Metro News
text:
Mark Brus for Metro.co.uk Thursday 16 Feb 2017 4:20 pm Arsene Wenger needs to stop Arsenal’s season falling apart (Picture: Getty) 
Arsenal manager Arsene Wenger has to get his team selection right in a challenging FA Cup tie away to non-league club Sutton United, says Martin Keown. Paul Pogba shows brotherly love after Florentin is forced off injured 
The Gunners’ season is hitting crisis point after recent defeats to Watford and Chelsea in the Premier League and last night’s 5-1 humiliation at the hands of Bayern Munich in the Champions League. 
Arsenal realistically have no trophy but the FA Cup left to play for between now and the end of the season, but such is their form, Keown has warned that they cannot take minnows Sutton lightly. Wenger’s side are surely heading out of the Champions League (Picture: Getty) 
After so many of his players let him down on Wednesday night, Wenger has been advised to think carefully about who to pick for Monday’s game at Sutton.
